HEADWORD: Epicoele
<hw>Ep"i*coele</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧p"⟦icr⟧*s⟦emac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>epi-</ets> + Gr. <grk>koi^lon</grk> a hollow.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A cavity formed by the invagination of the outer
wall of the body, as the atrium of an amphioxus and possibly the body
cavity of vertebrates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epicoene</ent>⟦br⟧
